text:
1:10:29 Shark fact: Did you know that the reason why most shark meat tastes bad and is harmful to eat outside of preparing it in a complex fermenting processes is because of the high amounts of urea stored in their bodies? Urea is a compound that separates into ammonia, water, CO2, and energy. Sharks use a high amount of urea in their tissue to maintain osmoregulation in a salt water environment - basically a fancy way to say: in order to not get dehydrated in salt water - but when they‚Äôre dead, that urea quickly dissolves into ammonia. That is the sole reason why their meat is so dangerous to humans when underprepared(sharks, already having natural ways to combat the compound being in their bodies, are obviously unaffected while eating the meat of other sharks).
Urea is also a major component of human urine, and is also the main reason why we urinate in the first place. So while it isn‚Äôt quite the exact same thing as urine, you can basically say sharks store pee in their tissue, and that most dishes containing shark have the main obstacle being to get said pee out of their tissue.
